  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment (NC-7 Not-accepted, clean package)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors scoped-out with documented rationale. Decision: Not accepted — the assessed discretization error factor achieved only Gradation 2 against a required Gradation 3 threshold, and the output comparison factor similarly fell one gradation short. Both shortfalls are marginal but together constitute an unresolved credibility gap that the assessment team judged insufficient for regulatory submission without remediation. No offset is claimed; the rejection is a direct response to the documented shortfalls.",
